      "filePath": "apps/workers/src/lib/retention-correlation.ts",
      "summary": "Pure math module that turns a YouTube audienceRetention curve into a per-round retention snapshot (retention at start/end and drop-off), reusing the same round timing the studio used to render the video.",
      "tags": ["utility", "analytics", "pure-function", "math"],
      "complexity": "moderate",
      "languageNotes": "retentionAtRatio implements manual linear interpolation over a sorted curve with clamping at both ends — a small but easy-to-get-wrong numerical routine, which is why it has dedicated unit tests."
